		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "The Light of Justice",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>The blind justice emits a beacon of light in a @Template[cone|distance:30], dealing @Damage[12d6[spirit]] damage to all affected creatures (@Check[will|dc:27] save). Once used, the blind justice can't use The Light of Justice again for [[/gmr 1d6 #Duration]]{1d6 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Target creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> Target creature takes half damage.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> Target creature takes full damage. If the creature is under an illusion or polymorph effect, the blind justice attempts to @[[/r d120+22]{counteract} that.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> as failure, but if the creature is under an illusion or polymorph effect, that effect is automatically disrupted.</p>",
